<div class="mdui-typo"><h1 id="terrible-adj">terrible <strong><em>adj</em></strong></h1>
<p>英 /'terəbl/    美 /'terəbl/  </p>
<h2 id="_1">释义</h2>
<h4 id="1">1.★ <strong>可怕的；令人不快的</strong></h4>
<p>making you feel afraid or shocked：</p>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>a terrible experience / nightmare
令人不悦的经历/噩梦</p></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>Envy is a most terrible thing, and would spoil anybody’s nature.
嫉妒是很可怕的东西，它会毁坏人的天性。</p><footer>—— 王尔德</footer></div>

<h4 id="2-horrible-awful">2.★ <strong>厉害的；猛烈的；非常严重的 (horrible / awful)：</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>a terrible storm / accident
猛烈的暴风雨/重大事故</p></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>I’d got a terrible flu, so I just stayed in bed.
我患了重感冒，所以卧床休息。</p></div>

<h4 id="3">3.★ <strong>[非正式用语] 坏透的；很糟的：</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>— How do you like the food here?
你觉得这里的饭菜怎么样?</p></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>— Well, the rice is terrible, but the vegetable soup is OK.
嗯，米饭很难吃，但是蔬菜汤还不错。</p></div></div>